Question?</span><hr size=1> im starting out with a chanter, fresh and brand new on a new server to be with my aunt and uncle who i just found out play EQ. <br>
My question is how much of a difference does CHA really make?<br>
and how much of a difference does the race make?<br>
will my race hold back from epic quest at all?<br>
<br>
im thinking a DE chanter would be a nice change of things from my old boring druid, but i cant be certain so i thought id ask the pro's. sorry there was no nOOb question board or i would have just gone there.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deltoran>Deltoran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(11/26/02 10:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question?</span><hr size=1> CHA makes a difference as you start to level up, but it is easy to get that up, and some nice buffs for cha and faction.  Lots of intel items out there also, but to start on new server unless you have Kpp leaves a low ac.  I suggest putting most in intel and once you get your jewelcraft up you can make some cats eye jewelry and raise your cha that way.  Most of the intel items for lower chars have lowsy AC!  CHA is important or I have noticed less fails at mezzing and charming with the higher it goes. (also helps with your prices)<br>
<br>
IF DE remember AGNOSTIC!!!! (can hide race but not religion)<br>
~Del~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skylaamacleod>SkylaaMacLeod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(11/26/02 1:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question?</span><hr size=1> I love my DE enchanter. When I created her I put max points in to INT and the rest into CHA.  I've not regretted that or my decision to make her agnostic.  Now at level 58, her INT is maxed at 255 and unbuffed her CHA stands at 144, and 194 buffed.  I've only really noticed a difference in charms with higher CHA.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ethariel>Ethariel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(11/26/02 1:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question?</span><hr size=1> CHR or not CHR, that is the question.....<br>
<br>
2 schools of thought, Yes it helps and No it does not !.<br>
<br>
I'm a believer in Yes, from personal experience if i keep mine at or just above 201 then I am quite lucky with charms and mezzes seem to stick more often.<br>
After clearing my log file some months back before a holiday to DAoC I found my mezzes were resisted about 5 to 7% less with CHR 201, ok this was only over 50 or so mezzes but even 1% more IMHO helps when a mob is doing its best to double/quad you for 200+ a pop !!<br>
<br>
Eth<br>
